wikipedia_page.main: John Reginald Head (15 July 1868 – 15 May 1949) was an English first-class cricketer, active from 1892–98, who played for Middlesex. He was born in Hackney and died in Folkestone.

response: *John Head (peace activist) (1927–2007), founded CALM, the New Zealand Campaign Against Landmines in 1993
